> Just curious, for next time: does the "right" tool do a better job of grabbing those circlip eyes?  I can see how beefier pliers would give better leverage and have the
> right span, but what makes 'em hold onto the clips better?

The tips that engage the holes in the circlip have a slight "hourglass"
shape, slightly large in diameter at the end than 1/8 inch from the end.
If the clip starts to slip on these, then then do slip onto the tip not
off.

